<br>
Gonna talk about XP groups.<br>
<br>
This morning I was making your normal everyday XP group in PoValor, nothing special. just a grind group, had a cleric, a shaman and me a 65 monk, so we need some DPS and a tank.<br>
<br>
/w Shadow 60 65 LFG all<br>
/w Paladin 60 65 LFG all<br>
<br>
There was a warrior standing right next to us, LFG.<br>
<br>
No one wanted him.<br>
<br>
The shaman didn't want him, the cleric didn't want him, and frankly I didn't want him. We didn't know him, we didn't know what AA or Gear he had, it was a totally non-personal view.<br>
<br>
We got a Shadowknight, who we waited 5 mins for to run to PoV.<br>
<br>
Ok admittedly, we took the warrior, after the SK arrived, but it was a charity position, we all felt bad about the fact that he was standing there looking for a group, none of us knew him we just felt bad about it. We told him straight up the SK will be tanking.<br>
<br>
Why?<br>
<br>
Taunt.<br>
<br>
SK tanks, Shaman slows, clerics CH's I am smacking out 130dps and nothing moves that mob, its stuck to the SK like glue.<br>
<br>
Warrior tanks, we chase the mob to the Shaman, then we chase the mob to the cleric, then I have to evade 3 times during the fight because I am getting aggro.<br>
<br>
Enraging Blow weapons i have seen in action, and they are excellent, this gives the warrior aggro, but as I have seen on this board from you, dual wielding is dying in PoP.<br>
<br>
A Paladin uses his massive 2hander, Stun, mob is his for pretty much the whole fight. SK uses his massive 2hander, Festering Darkness (no idea what it is just the message I see) and the mob is his for the entire fight.<br>
<br>
Warrior, has to bust out two Enraging Blow weapons, that are high end issues, so pretty low in delay, eating ripostes for breakfast, dinner and supper, and is taking twice as much healing just to keep alive. Double the healing to keep up, means double the down time later on.<br>
<br>
I have seen warriors with Flurry?  I am pretty sure the warrior I was talking to said it was that, as I actually noted that he was holding aggro well and he remarked he had the AA skill Flurry. but bear in mind, we still had some ping pong and i was still evading, just a lot less.<br>
<br>
Its not enough, it still doesn't compete with an SK or a Paladins ability to hold aggro consistently. There is NO ping pong at all, and I do not have to evade at all when we use these classes for MTs.<br>
<br>
After what happened this morning I felt I should come here and post something, no class in EQ should have to rely on being given a position in a group on the goodwil of the group members.<br>
<br>
We coud have been all hardcore this morning and got a ranger or a rogue for DPS and that warrior would probably still be standing at the GraveYard of Valor looking for a group.<br>
<br>
As a foornote, your board is confusing, I have no idea if there is a general section or if this is the general section or whether i have posted in the wrong place, if it is the wrong place i do apologise.<br>
<br>
Fong<br>
65th Monk <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Tragically I was an Only Twin</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->.</div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=glachum>Glachum</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_cooldude.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 29<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/24/03 12:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2815.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: A Monks View on Warriors.</span><hr size=1> These are things we already know, was there a point to your post?  Would you like us to do something?  Are you suggesting taunting strategy or a warrior taunt fix?  Basically, you re-hashed everything that warriors are unhappy with, only this time, it came from a monk. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :x --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/sick.gif ALT=":x"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p>Glachum McShlachum<br>
